ve had procs go off in consecutive swings, or not at all, but only timed with a swing of the weapon, and it doesn't even have to be a hit.<br>
<br>
Regardless, I think Muzzle is worth while as it upgrades every pet you have or will have. It upgrades every pet you encounter (I believe, does it work with shammy and BL pets?). Unless you chain cast, if you aren't giving your pet a muzzle (only 100mana) then you aren't playing your class to potential. <br>
<br>
In my opinion Muzzle as a spell is worth more than any equipment you can get for 5k. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eatbugs>Eatbugs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#333333>(12/20/02 5:21:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Haste effects prock rate?</span><hr size=1> It does work on Beastlord pets, and if I knew a Mage who was hesitating buying it for 5k because of the price I'd contribute 1k just to have another person around who could summon muzzles. I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>love</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> pet groups with Mages. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thedrunkenmage>The Drunken Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#333333>(12/27/02 6:48:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1731.topic&index=19>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Haste effects prock rate?</span><hr size=1> Every time a you (or your pet) swing a weapon, it has a chance to proc (does NOT have to hit).  So haste DOES increase the number of procs per unit time, because it increases the number of swings per unit time.  More swings (with the same chance of a proc) = more procs.<br>
<br>
But there is a very simple rule to use when looking at haste.  This includes ALL ranges of damage/delay and with or without procs.  Haste % increase is directly proportional to DPS increase.<br>
<br>
So, if it adds 11% haste, it adds 11% to melee DPS (including melee procs).<br>
